A Midsummer Night's Dream, Act 5, Scene 1, Line 333:
"O Sisters Three"
(Seems he knows about 'The Three Sisters')

Epitome of Leftist argument is to go pseudo-meta into dogmatic sociology, as a way of bracketing awkward realities. 
"We know the sort of people who think like this."
... "If you believe in Natural Selection you're probably frustrated at work."

"I would recommend this book to anyone looking to acquaint themselves with one of the most influential thinkers of our time." Can't link because X is retarded. Book Review: Noticing - by Jackson Jules (substack.com)
